---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const faqSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'FAQPage',
  mainEntity: [
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'Who is this report for?',
      acceptedAnswer: {
        '@type': 'Answer',
        text: 'This report is for HVAC owners who want to understand why competitors are winning more map pack visibility and likely capturing more inbound calls in the local market.',
      },
    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'What do you need from me?',
      acceptedAnswer: {
        '@type': 'Answer',
        text: 'We need your business name, city, primary service keyword, and Google Business Profile link. The report is built from public search results and visible profile data.',
      },
    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'Is this a call, pitch, or retainer?',
      acceptedAnswer: {
        '@type': 'Answer',
        text: 'No. This is a fixed-scope written deliverable. No discovery call, no agency pitch, and no ongoing retainer are required to get the report.',
      },
    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'What will I actually receive?',
      acceptedAnswer: {
        '@type': 'Answer',
        text: 'You receive a written PDF with your local map pack position, top competitor comparison, review and profile gaps, likely visibility implications, and three ranked priorities for what to fix first.',
      },
    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'How fast is delivery?',
      acceptedAnswer: {
        '@type': 'Answer',
        text: 'The report is delivered in writing within 48 hours after the market and scope are confirmed.',
      },
    },
  ],
};
---
<Layout
  title="HVAC Local Market Report | Competitor Gap Analysis for Owners | Built on Tenth"
  description="See how many calls stronger HVAC competitors may be taking from you each month with local visibility analysis, competitor comparison, and clear written priorities delivered in 48 hours."
  active="report"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqSchema)} />

  

  <div class="report-page">
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="page-wrap hero__grid">
        <div>
          <h1>See exactly how many calls your competitors are taking from you <em>every month.</em></h1>
          <p class="hero__body">
            This report shows where you rank in your local map pack, who is beating you,
            and how many calls you are likely losing because of it, in plain numbers you
            can use before spending another dollar on ads, agencies, or “fixes.”
          </p>

          <div class="hero__trust">
            <span>Used by HVAC owners before spending on ads or agencies</span>
            <span>Delivered in 48 hours</span>
            <span>No calls. No upsell. Just the report.</span>
          </div>

          <div class="page-actions">
            <a href="/apply?service=report&source=report-page" class="btn btn--primary">Request your report</a>
          </div>
          <a href="/tools" class="text-link">Explore HVAC calculators</a>

          <div class="hero__microcopy">Most HVAC companies we analyze are losing somewhere between 15 and 40 calls per month to stronger local competitors. This report shows whether you are one of them.</div>
        </div>

        <aside class="offer-card">
          <div class="offer-card__top">
            <div class="section-label">One-time report</div>
            <div class="offer-card__price">$200</div>
            <h3>HVAC Local Market Report</h3>
            <p class="offer-card__sub">Delivered in 48 hours. No calls. No upsell. No retainer. If there is no meaningful visibility gap, the report tells you that too.</p>
          </div>
          <ul class="offer-card__body">
            <li>Where you actually rank when customers search, not where you think you rank</li>
            <li>The exact companies taking calls before you and why</li>
            <li>The trust, review, and profile gaps visible in your market</li>
            <li>A rough estimate of how many calls you may be losing each month</li>
            <li>The first three fixes most likely to change the outcome</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="offer-card__foot">
            <p>The fastest way to know whether local visibility is actually the bottleneck before you spend another month or another budget cycle fixing the wrong thing.</p>
            <a href="/apply?service=report&source=report-page" class="btn btn--primary offer-card__cta">Request your report</a>
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="page-wrap proof__grid">
        <div>
          <div class="section-label">Why HVAC owners buy this</div>
          <h2>They already know something is off. They just cannot see <em>the gap clearly enough to act.</em></h2>
          <p class="section-intro">
            Calls feel inconsistent. Competitors keep showing up first. Reviews look thin.
            The report gives owners a fast answer before another month of calls goes to
            someone else.
          </p>

          <div class="proof__stats">
            <div class="proof-stat">
              <strong class="proof-stat__title proof-stat__title--blue">You are being compared already</strong>
              <p>Your market is choosing between you and the first few companies Google shows side by side.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="proof-stat">
              <strong class="proof-stat__title proof-stat__title--green">The cost is usually hidden</strong>
              <p>Most owners can feel the leak but cannot put a number on what it is costing every month.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="proof-stat">
              <strong class="proof-stat__title proof-stat__title--red">Clarity beats guessing</strong>
              <p>This helps you decide whether reviews, profile strength, or local rankings are the real problem before you spend more.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="proof__side">
          <div class="report-mock">
            <div class="report-mock__head">
              <span>What this actually looks like</span>
              <span>Local market preview</span>
            </div>
            <div class="report-mock__body">
              <span class="report-mock__sample">Sample snapshot</span>
              <h3>Dallas · AC repair</h3>
              <p>Apex Comfort Systems compared with the companies Google is showing before them when local buyers search.</p>
              <div class="report-mock__table">
                <div class="report-mock__row">
                  <strong>Cool Breeze HVAC</strong>
                  <span>4.9</span>
                  <span>847 rev</span>
                  <span>#1</span>
                </div>
                <div class="report-mock__row">
                  <strong>Texas Air Experts</strong>
                  <span>4.8</span>
                  <span>612 rev</span>
                  <span>#2</span>
                </div>
                <div class="report-mock__row">
                  <strong>One Hour Heating</strong>
                  <span>4.7</span>
                  <span>439 rev</span>
                  <span>#3</span>
                </div>
                <div class="report-mock__row report-mock__row--you">
                  <strong>Apex Comfort Systems</strong>
                  <span>4.3</span>
                  <span>91 rev</span>
                  <span>#4</span>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="report-mock__foot">
                <span>Estimated monthly calls going to stronger local competitors first</span>
                <strong>+38 calls/mo</strong>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section--muted">
      <div class="page-wrap">
        <div class="section-label">What is inside</div>
        <h2>You are not buying a report. You are buying <em>clarity on the loss.</em></h2>
        <p class="section-intro">
          The deliverable is intentionally narrow and useful. It is designed to help you
          see the local problem, quantify it, and decide what to fix first.
        </p>

        <div class="deliverables__grid">
          <article class="deliverable-card">
            <h3>Where you actually rank when customers search</h3>
            <p>Not where you hope you rank. Not what a vendor told you. Where you are actually showing up in the local pack for the search that matters.</p>
            <ul class="deliverable-list">
              <li>The keyword and city snapshot that matters most</li>
              <li>Visible ranking context against real competitors</li>
              <li>A plain explanation of what that likely means</li>
            </ul>
          </article>

          <article class="deliverable-card">
            <h3>The exact companies taking calls before you</h3>
            <p>You see the businesses your market is comparing you against and the visible signals they have stacked better than you right now.</p>
            <ul class="deliverable-list">
              <li>Review count and rating context</li>
              <li>Profile completeness and trust signals</li>
              <li>The visible reasons they are likely winning first click</li>
            </ul>
          </article>

          <article class="deliverable-card">
            <h3>A rough estimate of the calls you may be losing</h3>
            <p>The number will never be perfect, but it gives owners the missing piece they usually want most: what the visibility gap is probably costing in inbound demand.</p>
            <ul class="deliverable-list">
              <li>Call-loss framing in business terms</li>
              <li>Three ranked priorities on what to fix first</li>
              <li>A clearer next step for your team or vendor</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section--muted">
      <div class="page-wrap outcome__grid">
        <article class="fit-card">
          <div class="section-label">What happens after you get this</div>
          <h3>Most owners use it to make the next decision with less waste.</h3>
          <p>Once the local picture is clear, the next move gets much easier to make.</p>
          <ul class="faq-list">
            <li>Decide if SEO or GBP work is actually worth fixing first</li>
            <li>See whether reviews are the main trust gap</li>
            <li>Understand whether stronger competitors are simply more visible locally</li>
            <li>Avoid wasting money on the wrong solution next month</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <figure class="report-media-card report-media-card--context">
          <img src="/images/brand/hvac/blog-how-much-should-hvac-company-spend-on-marketing-2026.png" alt="HVAC owner reviewing marketing budget notes, invoices, and booked-job numbers at a desk" loading="lazy" />
          <figcaption>Built for the decisions that happen when an owner is trying to figure out whether the budget, the map pack, or the competition is really the problem.</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="page-wrap fit__grid">
        <article class="fit-card">
          <div class="section-label">Best fit</div>
          <h3>This is best when you need a fast answer before spending more.</h3>
          <p class="fit-card__lead">It works best when you suspect the local market is the issue, but you do not yet have enough clarity to know what deserves attention first.</p>
          <ul class="faq-list">
            <li>You are getting calls, but not enough</li>
            <li>You suspect competitors are outranking you locally</li>
            <li>You want clarity before spending more on ads or agencies</li>
            <li>You want a written answer, not another meeting</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="fit-card fit-card--alt">
          <div class="section-label">Not for</div>
          <h3>If you already know local visibility is not the issue, this is too narrow.</h3>
          <p class="fit-card__lead">This report is not trying to diagnose every part of the business. It is a local market visibility decision tool first.</p>
          <ul class="faq-list">
            <li>You already know your visibility is strong</li>
            <li>You need sales, CSR, website, and lead-source diagnostics together</li>
            <li>You are looking for an agency retainer or management service</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="page-wrap">
        <div class="section-label">How it works</div>
        <h2>No calls. No meetings. <em>Three simple steps.</em></h2>
        <p class="section-intro">The process is intentionally blunt and fast.</p>

        <div class="process__grid">
          <article class="process-card">
            <div class="process-card__num">01</div>
            <h3>Send your business + keyword</h3>
            <p>Give us your business name, city, main service keyword, and Google Business Profile link.</p>
          </article>

          <article class="process-card">
            <div class="process-card__num">02</div>
            <h3>We analyze your market</h3>
            <p>We look at the local map pack, the companies showing before you, and the visible review, trust, and profile gaps.</p>
          </article>

          <article class="process-card">
            <div class="process-card__num">03</div>
            <h3>You get the report in 48 hours</h3>
            <p>You receive a written PDF showing the gap, the likely impact, and the first fixes worth making.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="page-wrap faq__grid">
        <div class="faq-stack">
          <article class="faq-card">
            <div class="section-label">FAQ</div>
            <h3>What do you need from me?</h3>
            <p>Your business name, city, main keyword, and GBP link. We are not asking for internal dashboards, ad account access, or a long questionnaire.</p>
          </article>

          <article class="faq-card">
            <h3>Is this a call or a pitch?</h3>
            <p>No. This page is meant to convert without requiring a meeting. The report itself is delivered in writing, and the intake stays written-first too.</p>
          </article>

          <article class="faq-card">
            <h3>Will I know exactly what to do after?</h3>
            <p>You will know the local visibility problem more clearly and get three ranked priorities. That is enough for most owners to decide whether to act internally, with a vendor, or go deeper later.</p>
          </article>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-card faq-card--support">
          <div class="section-label">Why this is easy to say yes to</div>
          <h3>The scope is tight, the price is simple, and the outcome is obvious.</h3>
          <p>
            You finally get a clear answer on whether stronger local competitors are
            quietly routing calls away from you, without signing up for another call,
            another retainer, or another vague diagnostic.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="cta-card-section">
      <div class="page-wrap">
        <div class="cta-card cta-card--report">
          <div class="cta-card__inner">
            <div class="cta-card__label">Get started</div>
            <h2 class="cta-card__title">See the gap before another month of calls goes to <em>someone else.</em></h2>
            <p class="cta-card__body">
              If competitors are outranking you, this report will make the gap visible.
              If local visibility is not the issue, that is useful too. Either way,
              you leave with a clearer next move than “try more marketing.”
            </p>
            <div class="cta-card__actions">
              <a href="/apply?service=report&source=report-page" class="btn btn--primary">Request your report</a>
            </div>
            <div class="cta-card__meta">Delivered in 48 hours. No call required.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>
